    Author:
    Communote GmbH - http://www.communote.com/

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • HTML

        public static final NoteRenderMode HTML
        the note content should be rendered in a generic HTML format, i.e. the HTML should not contain JavaScript or custom CSS classes. To provide additional meta data to clients, HTML data attributes can be used.

      • PLAIN

        public static final NoteRenderMode PLAIN
        the note content should be rendered as plain text

      • PORTAL

        public static final NoteRenderMode PORTAL
        the notes are rendered by the web frontend and thus can contain custom JavaScript calls available in the frontend

      • REPOST

        public static final NoteRenderMode REPOST
        The rendered note will be used to prepare an editor for creating a repost to this note. The content is expected to be HTML but must not contain JavaScript. This mode should be used if the editor is HTML capable.

      • REPOST_PLAIN

        public static final NoteRenderMode REPOST_PLAIN
        The rendered note will be used to prepare an editor for creating a repost to this note. The content is expected to be plain text.

    • Field Detail

      • PLAIN_MODE_OPTION_KEY_BEAUTIFY

        public static final String PLAIN_MODE_OPTION_KEY_BEAUTIFY
        Key for a mode option to inform the pre-processors that the plain text version of the content should be beautified (e.g. indent LIs). This option should only be considered as set if the value is "true".
